it is a experimental, avant garde and surreal performance. we use a combination of sounds, movement and music. citizens of the gray or this dark thing that sleeps in me is a theatrical production generated by the curiosity of how the relationship between man and woman has evolved throughout the years and how this relationship has become a struggle for power; a fight to death where there can be only one winner. 
the play portrays a world which is deeply correlated with the the #metoo movement!

there is no dialogue, nor text in this play. it traspases  language  barriers in such a way that any person from any country can understand it, given its universal codes.

at the theater for the new city, ny. 
dates: nov. 9th-25th
visit: https://bit.ly/2nfevgd to get your tickets now.
www.citizensofthegray.com #actor #theatre #creandoco #nyc
name: Gustavo Ramirez

about being a bad guy and manipulated me into comforting him. he texted me again a few months after and i told him to shove it. my junior year, at the very beginning, i started talking to a graduate student. he gave me creepy vibes since we met. but even after i told my friend, i gave him a second chance. we went on a coffee date, he then got up and told me we were going to his place. i tried to get out of it by telling him jokingly that i was going to stay there. but i was scared of him and went. i asked him to just sit. i sat in the single seat. he randomly threw himself and me and started making out with me. he made my lip go numb. i pushed him and said i was uncomfortable, stared at the wall. he did it over and over again, then began to touch me all over. he pushed me onto the floor and got on top of me. i had my hood over me and was moving my face away. he eventually got off and persisted with the making out every 5 mins regardless of my protests. i was able to leave after 4 hours and after he told me he loved cocaine. i filed against him. we'll see what happens. text:
warning: sexual assault/harassment/rape

so i can say that college can be a rough ride. first semester i had 2 tas, one for chemistry lab and one for chemistry theory. i thought the one from my theory class was pretty cute, we spent a lot of time together because i couldn't make his office hours so we would tirelessly go through all the homework questions together in the library. i was talking to him after an exam review one day, he sits next to me and tells me his sister was going to buy a perfume that smells of me. after i got through that class he would still stare at me, my friends would point out a guy looking at me when we were in random places, and there he would be. he finally graduated last year. my other ta was less mild, we joked around in our lab section, i would email him about lab reports at random times. he then gave me his number over the school email. he wasn't done when the semester ended. he would text me over winter break and started insinuating that i needed to blow him. i stopped talking to him after that. i showed up to class after winter break and he was my ta again, and he looked so smug. i've calculated those chances, it was around 1000th of a percent. i avoided office hours, but i was too scared to change sections because the only one i could make was in the same room with a different ta. i was scared to tell him i had a boyfriend because i thought he would fail me. he even had the guts to email me the start of the year after. that was when it started getting worse. during my first semester i met a guy, he was in my math discussion and lecture. i finally asked him for his name because he was giving me answers i didn't ask for and kept sitting next me in all our joint classes. he asked me to study physics, i told him no. one day i was studying at the library, i came back from the bathroom and he was sitting next to my desk. he told me he knew which floor i was on and deduced where i sat by looking at the angles on my instagram picture. (1/3)  #nomore #metoo #metoomovement
name: #metoo

text:
duality: "church house confessions" explores the inner battle we all face. saint or sinner? fight or flight? love or fear? we are tested every day of our lives. the universe asks us what we will do with what we have. the experience is uniquely our own. in that realization, shouldn't we see we're essentially the same? 
in these trying times, it's so important to remember where we came from and the privilege we all have in varying degrees. it's easy to point to those who have "more." but for someone else(that closeted gay kid, that rape victim who chose silence out of fear, that refugee whose family was ripped apart, that parent who lost a child to gun violence, or family that lost everything in a raging fire or flood) we are fortunate. i constantly have to remind myself that i am lucky to have what i have, even when it's far from my  projected goal. grappling with that duality. that reminder to stop and appreciate the present vs the nagging obsession with a future. so many people are in my thoughts right now. but thinking (and praying) aren't helping anyone. if you can, give to those communities who need it. volunteer, donate and speak up and vote. stay vigilant, famâœŠ

i've joined play it forward, which allows artists to donate their songs to charity. 100% of proceeds from downloads will go to communities in need. check out my profile(link in bio), download a track and give back all at the same time! i hope to find other artists to join me in making a larger impact, through collaborations, remixes and live performances. if you're a producer, musician or artist in the bay area and interested, please pm meâ¤ï¸
.
.
"there is no dreaming too big. what people can do together is so much more powerful than what they can do by themselves" .
.

text:
bringing awareness of abuse to the forefront.
itâ€™s not gender biased or age biased. abuse is not okay!! the statistics from the australian institute of health and welfare report that one in five women and one in twenty men are sexually abused or threatened after the age of fifteen. one in six girls and one in nine boys are abused during childhood and early adolescence. 
this is a shocking reality in our communities across australia.  how many of us are truly aware of the impact this has on not only the individual but society as a whole? 
we are putting together a book on the impact of trauma and abuse in childhood, and the ongoing effect it has on the mind, body and soul. 
this is the story of one womanâ€™s account of the events that shaped her world. the enormity of her story will bring awareness and inspiration to others that have been touched by the crime of abuse. 
i believe when we stand together as a community, we stand stronger, dignified, and powerful. letâ€™s break the silence! #itsnotokay.

here is a game. never have i ever felt like saying no to giving someone my number was going to put my life in jeopardy. i am not shocked when i hear about murders such as mary spears a woman who was gunned down after saying no (she had a fiance present at the time of her murder not that it mattered). i'm not shocked because i choose to take the wool from my eyes and see the violence of men that exist in this world. i choose to listen and believe the stories of women with a #metoo or not. now i know not all men are like this but all men are capable and more than enough lives are lost to the ones who do so i hope i don't get any of those comments. even my wife has a horrifying story that makes my blood boil with rage. it touches so many women in our lives and thus it is our problem as men, it is our problem because we keep doing it and perpetuating these disgusting acts on women. what can we do to stop it? well first stop pretending it is made up when a woman tells these stories. look at yourself in the mirror and realise your part in it. educate yourself and stand up. you are not entitled to anyone elses body but your own. i feel so much sorrow in my heart for this shit and i hope people google search mary spears, or maren sanchez and learn about these very true situations where life has been senslessly stolen due to misogyny and entitlement .
#colormyflaws #violence #bodypositive #art #artoftheday #mysogony

itâ€™s sitting on the kitchen floor wishing you were someone else, anyone!

-
stop romanticising depression.
-

.
today, we ask attendees to carry a white rose while we march, in order to symbolize our solidarity with the victims and our hope for a better future.

-

-

text: i have seen accounts where the entire feed is selfies with an overlay of spiritual & uplifting messages. there are times when a selfie with an uplifting overlay makes sense, but far too often, i see carefully crafted selfies or even just photographs taken of someone looking amazing made into a meme with a spiritual message over their photo. thatâ€™s when i think to myself, why donâ€™t they just create an account specifically devoted to their self photos? and another one with awesome memes? mostly, these ladies are thin & â€œmodel-perfectâ€ looking, and iâ€™ll get a follow based on one of my ed-related hashtags. so as with every new follower, i click on their account to see if they are worthy of seeing me baring my soul and sharing recovery journey. most of the time, i have to block them, and so many times, i have to see these - very thing that ed looooves to use as one of my triggers. so, this is yet one more way to protect my feed, not just the things i will see, but the things that others will see about my experience in life. my precious soul. #selfies #selfiesteem #narcissisticselfie #narcissistsofinstagram #eatingdisorderrecovery #soul #selflove #healing #upliftingquotes #bodylove #empoweringwomen #mentalhealthawareness #womeninspiringwomen #empowerment #lifecoach #reinventyourself #meditation #quotestoliveby #positivememes #followers #inspirationalquotes #quotes #strongwomen #ed #fuckoffed #anorexia #striveforgreatness #selfawareness #metoo #universe thank you @sacredizeyourlife for keeping it real.

text:
*credits unknown*
he betrayed me. he broke me into a million pieces. it was as if someone had cut me open, slashed deeply into each of my organs and stitched me back up again to live a nightmare-bleeding from the inside out. i didnâ€™t know i had become a statistic for a crime that you never hear about.

we, as a society, hear the word rape and picture a woman being attacked in a dark alley by some drifter. we, as media-educated drones, envision a college co-ed going to a party and being assaulted by a gang of frat boys. we, as women, imagine some sicko holding a knife to our throats to get what he wants. is that rape? you bet. but, all those scenarios account for only a minor 20-30% of rapes.

that leaves 80-70% of rapes that donâ€™t fit the stereotype. huh? how can we not know what most rapes are like? that doesnâ€™t make any sense. what we know as rape isnâ€™t the majority. why? how can it be that so many rapes committed arenâ€™t what we know rape to be? no one wants to talk about real rape. no one wants to put it out there for discussion. no one wants to admit that our society has a large majority of rapes that are unspeakable, let alone unthinkable. or even worse, society just doesnâ€™t think the majority is as bad as the stereotype. if thatâ€™s the case, weâ€™re dead wrong-every last one of us.

#sexualharassment #sexualabuse #rapeculture #rapesurvivor #rape #survivor #letustalk #opendialogue #metoomovement #metoo #metooindia #staystrong

text:
hans montenegro - like youâ€™ve never heard him before. always honest, pointed, insightful and brutally frank.

here are some of the memorable things that he said:

1.  on the #metoo movement. â€œna molestiya ako noong 13 years old ako. i didnâ€™t feel good about not doing anything then. coming forward with my story and learnings will hopefully inspire victims to understand that there is strength in numbers and that we should support each other; and for our colleagues in power to sanction the perpetrators. â€œ
2. on his daughter ashley (by cara subijano) i am happy that cara and i and her new partner are ok and are good co-parents with me to our daughter who has decided to stay and live with me and my wife (marilen faustino). ashley is showing inclinations of becoming a beauty queen, but i want her to train and finish her studies first. 
3. hans corrected a gma online report, â€œi donâ€™t have a son by maritoni fernandez.â€ our conversation tonight is one for the books. watch the interview in my fb account or at the level up showbiz saturdate page.

thank you hans for the trust and the friendship all these years. it was a good updating; sa uulitin!

text:
looking back at the ceo: 
once upon a time there was an ambitious young lady who set her path with her head held high, strike of confidence and personality. i use to think that was me, back in those days, just landed my first job and all i wanted to do in five years is to be a ceo. well 10 years later, look at me i am nowhere close to that. 
the truth is, i could be a ceo if i dare enough to jump, i could be a ceo if i quit my current job and start my own company, i could be a ceo if my disorders doesn't bother me or even exist. i could be if.... but far from what i had ever imagined, being a ceo of myself is what i am. i am my own ceo if you count me surviving my daily struggle. i am ceo of myself when i am in control. i am my own ceo if i can be the best that i can be everyday. 
i don't need to be a ceo to proof that i completed sets of challenges for the day. i am already successful when i decide to wake up, when i decide to go forward, when i decide it's ok to be unique, when i decide to go and move along! 
maybe one day i will become a ceo of the norm, chief executive officer of a company or maybe i would be a ceo of my own home. may god bless us all. 
#imok  #selfhelp #tryingmybest #everydayisanewday #metoo #mybest

#candoit #motivation

text:
focus now: 
now...always remember the now! never much about the past or never more about the future. always the now!

it's hard to do this when you are bipolar, because you mind keeps on running like loose cargo train. sometime it could also feel like you are in a spiral staircase that never ends. so this is when my medication regime helps. it makes me focus and it makes me focus on the now. 
my dad always tell me to stop taking those medication, but i never listen because i love him, i love my husband, my daughter, my family and i want to be in the now, to be here and to be alive. i want to make sure i can live in the moment and stop worrying about the past or the future. 
so people of the world, live in the now, live in the moment and forever cherishes the little time we have left.

text:
the future will remain unknown: 
there are just so many things we could do to achieve our goals and life targets. so many plans we could make but at the end our destiny rely with god, the creator. but i should never forget to keep on trying everyday, to be the best everyday, and to continuously do the best that i could at everything every single time so that my future would be in my palms. that is what i tell myself everyday. you can do it! strike a pose, have faith and take the journey to the unknown.

text:

text:
look into the eyes
of your childhood
you know now
what you knew then
that child is you
remember what
you went through
how you smiled and danced
and sang anyway
but slept with a knife
under your pillow
or glued the lock
to your bedroom door
all to no avail
- laurie maren

#sttop2start #lauriemarentransformation #metoo #itsnotyourfault

text:
hey guys! i will be a guest panelist during howard homecoming. please come out and support!! friday, october 26, 2018 at 1:30pm
the film begins promptly at 2pm. 26 minutes in length.

an rsvp for this free event is requested at https://laloshousefilmscreening.eventbrite.com by wednesday, october 24.

the howard alumni band, bedolove, and chronicle vision present a special film screening of a 2018 student academy award winner â€œlaloâ€™s houseâ€! all are welcome to join us and witness this amazing film, meet the inspirational kelley kali, and engage in a lively and informative panel discussion following the screening. light fare and refreshments will be served by sinfully wright catering. donations are welcome.

about the award-winning documentary:
as a writer, producer, and director of â€œlaloâ€™s houseâ€, kelley kali has created a poignant film inspired by true events, telling the story of two young haitian sisters who unknowingly get trapped in a child trafficking ring. the film includes gracelle beauvais (the jamie foxx show, spider-man 2017, and white house down) who is an executive producer and actress. and, includes jimmy jean-louis from â€œclawsâ€. trailer: https://vimeo.com/243611573; https://revolt.tv/videos/insider-access-women-lalos-house-detail-importance-bringing-awareness-sex-trafficking-00810db2; http://www.laloshousefilm.com/

text:
mental health is self-care
____________________________
the 6 areas of our lives that requires constant replenishing are... â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”-
1.physical self-care
basic physical needs. exercise. pampering yourself. embracing your senses. doing make sure body feels good & relaxed
___________________________
2. emotional self-care
processing emotions in a healthy way. cultivating emotional intelligence. having good coping mechanisms. feeling your feelings.
____________________________
3. personal self-care
getting to know yourself. try new things. spending time alone. making time for hobbies. having goals for yourself.
__________________________
4. social self-care
getting the amount of social interaction that feels good. creating good boundaries. working on friendships.
â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”
5. spiritual self-care
figuring out your beliefs. reading books on spirituality. prayer. seeking community. challenging your spiritual ideas.
____________________________
6. practical self-care
finances. chores. healthy work boundaries.

text: inspired by therapist #marisapeer watching an interview with author/entrepreneur #lewishowes on his show #theschoolofgreatness (youtube) i wrote a little note to myself ğŸ™‚ in the interview marisa talked about the main struggle we all face - the feeling of â€˜iâ€™m not enoughâ€™ - we tend to talk to ourselves negatively a lot and itâ€™s the words we use that have a great impact on our wellbeing - she talks about how our thoughts can either heal us or kill us, quite literally too - that what we say manifests as our reality, including physical diseases. when we continuously push feelings away instead of sitting with them and feeling it, expressing it in some way and understanding them, this is when these feelings manifest in different negative ways and cause serious harm to ourselves, also impacting on others and our environment. marisa emphasised how important positive self talk is, especially to remind yourself that we are enough. as i struggle with perfectionism i find it so helpful to express myself creatively and to write things down, including little notes to myself - feeling a bit flat today so i gave myself a little reminder and hopefully it helps others too. marisaâ€™s practice involves writing on your mirror - i am enough or on a piece of paper and sticking it around the house - a great way to remind ourselves to be kind to ourselves especially as it can be so hard sometimes, i have to really work on this after years of beating myself up massively but itâ€™s all about the process and so worth it ğŸ§¡ğŸŒ¼ #trusttheprocess #perfectionism #perfect #imperfect #perfectlyimperfect #youareenough #bekind #selfkindness #selflove #selfcare #change #positiveselftalk #positivethoughts #youarenotalone #itsok #itsoktonotbeok #knowyourself #expressyourself #creative #creativeprocess #metoo #youmatter #anxietywarrior #wellbeing #feelings

text:
the phycologist: 
a new type of therapy that i am trying, before this we had gone to neurologist, psychiatrist and hypnotherapist. last week we embark on something new, a phsycologist. to differentiate; a neurologist is a medical doctor that specialized in brains, psychiatrist is a medical doctor specialized in mental disorders, a hypnotherapist does not need to be a doctor but have certification in hypnoteraphy and they hypnotized you or your unconscious mind to be better, and a phsycologist is someone that uses counseling sessions and phsycotheraphy. 
so this young chap we met was kinda cool. he thaught my case was very interesting and my coping mechanism is very unique. he doesn't judge or make funny faces when me or azhar tells him stuffs that had happened. at first i was worried because he looked so young he would be more judgmental and less experienced, but because he was cool and open minded i wouldn't mind seeing him again once a week for the next 5 weeks. even if he doesn't know how to deal with me, i hope that he would do his research and figure things out before our next session. best of luck for all of us... #imok #selfhelp #tryingmybest #everydayisanewday

text:
what are you doing in your community to help prevent child sexual abuse?

don't just sympathize with victims and their parents. get up and do something about it!

ok  i understand, you don't have the skill but you have passion. passion is key! now, the next step is to get trained! 
yes, training will strengthen your passion. thank god you have an opportunity to get the necessary skills at the child sexual abuse awareness and prevention workshop taking place on 1st december 2018 in lagos.

call +2348027835885 for registration details.

thanks to @pius.adegoke and @adegokeyeni for taking the bold step to educate parents about their roles in the prevention of child sexual abuse in porthatcourt. god bless you!

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
medusa, wronged and accused,
has walked out of the myth,
to the reality of our times,
in the atmosphere of clouded acceptance.
she is no more the gorgon,
but the wronged beauty
whose wings were clipped,
by the powers of lust.
she is out to avenge
for the wrong done
let's not consider her courageous head
as trophy to be blunted.
and hunt her till she becomes a myth again.
one thing in the myth is right,
even today her anger shimmers,
turning the power that be to stone at her gaze. Â check my next post for continuation of this. thanks.

text:
check my previous post please.

i came across this powerful statue by luciano garbati in quartz and was spellbound of the artist's version of the inversion of a myth.

a statue speaks the minds of a billion people. this one screams at you with the urgency of a message delivered at the right time. this should provide courage in time of need. this shatters everything.

though, this was ten years old, maybe, as they say one can't stop an idea whose time has come. medusa has arrived and how?

with that angry gaze, a sword in her left hand and a severed head in her right, a symbolic representation of how wronged feel.

it feels as if the sculptor had inured this version in his mind, his hands looking into the mind chiselled away the rest bringing to life the imagined medusa

text:
vivid, perceptive, timely, and ridiculously entertaining, seduction is a landmark work that examines women, sex, and male power in hollywood during its golden age - a legacy that endures nearly a century later.

karina longworth (creator of the @youmustrememberthis podcast) reminds us, long before the harvey weinsteins there was howard hughes-the texas millionaire whose reputation as a cinematic provocateur was matched only by that as a prolific womanizer.

text:
i see - a girl whose heart belongs to the ocean on one of the happiest days of her life. taken before she dove right back in after an exhaustive first surf sesh.
you see - a four lettered word you love using to shame girls because they are wearing something you can't - even if they may be the most clothed person on the shore - and you're uncomfortable.
don't worry i've notified the lifeguards to allow sarees for your next visit there. but beware, your stomach will show while mine doesn't. and i'll be there, ready to scream out my four lettered word. love.
#weshouldallbefeminists #metoo

text:
history repeats itself and the wise learn from the past to not be yesterdays fool tomorrow.

last year, i was fired from this grocer for standing up to the racist good ol boys (mgmt and their literal nazi customer friend) and reporting sexual harassment from the married with kid, trump obsessed, manager. (they were about to give me a raise, but i got something better that day: my wonderful dog)

i laughed my way home.

i now make 2 to 3 times as much and will be able to ask for more because i'm worth it and not a soul can deny that.

yesterday, i was fired a few days after reporting the sexual harassment (quid pro quo and so on) from two chefs (main one also with a kid and from a deep red state, fired from his last job) and incessant verbal abuse from their boss, and illegal orders to work off the clock and and condoning of the other behavior and pseudo racism by their boss.

i laughed my way out of the door. would you believe they said they were a professional environment?

it's only been a day and i'm having trouble picking between wonderful places with wonderful and kind people that want me to work with them as much as i wish to work with them.

i have a feeling that since this very same pattern of events has repeated itself (third time in 2 years), what may be pictured may soon befall some aspect of where i was illegally ousted.

who's to say? i'm going to work somewhere that doesnt forget my paycheck. (i'm not going to name names unless you have to know just because i don't like to trash even my worst enemies or more than necessary)

you better believe i got the last laugh and cackling like a hyena taking these pictures, too!

#itsthelittlethings #everyvictorycounts #fightracism #redstatesarefullofhate #kitchenconfidential
#cheftalk #cooklife #boh #kitchentalk #industry #cookstories #chefstories #retailsucks #metoo #eeoc #enoughisenough #nomeansno #justiceserved #kitchennightmares

text:
this racism scale is a tremendous tool to ground a healthy discussion of #raceequity, and pinpoint your personal, group, institutional & structural maturity. 
there has never been one issue, policy, or concern in the united states of america that isn't grounded in & influenced by the myth of white male superiority. not one. not back then. not now. 
the most important questions we all must ask ourselves are:

1. where do i fall on this scale relating to #indigenouspeople?

2. where do i fall on this scale relating to #africanamericans?

think you're #woke? think again. 
think i forgot about your #affinity? think again. 
no matter your identity, every single issue, policy, or concern you have in the united states of america could be resolved by answering those 2 questions & moving further to the lower right. 
if you say love is the answer, i'll say love is that far bottom right corner. 
you can't name one news story or societal ill that couldn't be resolved by creating equity in the way we treat natives, and when i say blacks, i particularly mean the descendants of those who were enslaved. think about it. i'll wait.

tell me. where do you fall on this scale for question 1 & 2? i'll share my past & current in the comments 
download a pdf version of this racism scale directly from the creators at https://racismscale.weebly.com

text:
i had an amazing time yesterday, but i am absolutely bone weary and wiped out today. i canâ€™t believe i pushed through three decades of my life like this; having my energy levels plummet after an event and then not even allowing myself time to decompress from the sensory and social overload because no one else seemed similarly affected.

the only reason i lasted yesterday evening is because eventually i was able to retreat to a quiet corner for the last few hours. this morning i even made it to the post-wedding barbecue. i donâ€™t know why this tradition exists, if itâ€™s just a new zealand thing or if it happens everywhere. i canâ€™t understand why the bride and groom would want to organise yet another gathering the day after something as high maintenance as a wedding.

almost no one has been more understanding of my needs than my partnerâ€™s group of friends. i didnâ€™t expect this from them, iâ€™ve always known them to be a bunch of very typical kiwi blokes. they have taken a lot of initiative making sure events are accessible to me post diagnosis and that iâ€™m never pressured to stay longer than i can. itâ€™s really sweet.

i took a while to fall asleep when i got back, that happens sometimes when iâ€™m overloaded and need sleep the most. when i finally did sleep i had an awful dream about an email from an hr lady.

complex traumas operate like that, the most mundane and unremarkable of occurrences trigger all manner of threat detection and fight or flight responses. i woke up with my heart beating strangely, upset that something like panic over emails had reached me here.

i retreated back to the sea this afternoon. an attempt to douse ashes that evidently havenâ€™t finished smouldering.

womenâ€™s reproductive health has always been a passion of mine. i wanted to create a community for brown women to talk about reproductive health and sex education because we did not have a space for that growing up, and still donâ€™t. i approached zuni with the idea to make this happen and she jumped right on board. working at planned parenthood, i realized there was a distinct difference in health literacy regarding reproductive health. education about reproductive and sexual health topics are lacking in the south asian community. letâ€™s talk about the taboo topics in our community, letâ€™s engage in conversations about topics the brown aunties donâ€™t want us to talk about. letâ€™s end the stigma. 
go follow @thescarletjournal to learn more and leave a comment about what we can discuss!

text:
to everyone who sent support in response to my ig stories, thank you. my heart was beating so fast last night every time i fired off my replies. it beat fast when i shared the screenshots here on ig and again when i made a public post on fb (because the original one was removed). it was scary defending myself in a public setting. but i wasnâ€™t standing up for just myselfâ€”i was standing up for women everywhere.
.
several people encouraged me to do more. call out his full name, tell his wife, tell his boss. i couldnâ€™t do it. because even though he did something offensive, i still took his feelings and livelihood into consideration. and also, because i feared retaliation. see, this is a challenge women face that men donâ€™t even have to think about.
.
i am happy i was able to speak my peace, and whatâ€™s more, i am happy to have this platform to help educate and promote change. even though the original fb post was removed, along with my last reply to him, i hope he saw what i said. i hope he realizes the gravity of his actions and recognized his ignorance. i hope he grows from this. because defending unwarranted and inappropriate emojis is basically a gateway drug. itâ€™s a step before d*** pics, and if itâ€™s not called out, worse forms of sexual harassment are sure to follow.
.
to all the men who stood with me today: i am beyond grateful for you. â€œbehind every woke man is an exhausted feminist.â€ please continue keeping your friends (and strangers) in check, and donâ€™t let bad behavior slide. help them grow. every single woman in your life will benefit!
.
to all my ladies: donâ€™t be afraid to stand up for yourself! call out anyone who makes you feel uncomfortable. and also, support other women. we have enough men out there who still think itâ€™s okay to gaslight and harass us; we do not need to add to it. #metoo

i just wanna run away or die because i don't know how to deal with everything.

text:
when i was launching my clothing line in the spring, @cbtrn was recommended to me as photographer. i had never worked with him personally but liked him at events i was at. on set he was highly professional, but he also wouldâ€™ve had no choice because he was never alone with models and models were prepped by myself and my team.

iâ€™m so sickened to learn that this very trust and community exposure was used to trick women into shoots alone with him where he could start his pattern of assault escalation. this is a predator. read @gigisplendid and @cerclecheung for their stories and numerous others on the thread.

i felt very trusting of him after my shoot. i wouldâ€™ve recommended him! i want to share what i did as a business owner today with this information, in case it helps others in my position. this is by no means the only or the right reaction, just what makes sense to me. i reached out to my models and shoot team first thing to tell them about it and ask how they felt about the photos now. there was support to keep the photos up since i paid for them and remove his credits. i have done this. i have made a decision to not move forward posting more of these because unfortunately i will associate them with a heinous person. although i straight up canâ€™t afford it, iâ€™m looking into a new shoot because itâ€™s important to me, which my models have graciously offered to once again participate in.

this stirred up some real emotion for me. towards the end of college, i was assaulted in a situation where i felt extremely trusting and was very vulnerable. instead of the reaction iâ€™d always told myself i would have (kick their ass) i instead froze, and deflected and eventually just gave in & up hoping it would be over soon. i had only slept with 1 person, my college boyfriend, and i felt so angry that this was next. angry at myself. i felt so ashamed and so stupid and that i had actually been in control and failed. i didnâ€™t even define it as assault because i didnâ€™t have a reference for it. to this day, only a handful of people know this and itâ€™s almost 15 years later. this was hard to share, but i hope this encourages more people to feel they can speak out. #metoo

text:
well, and wow....thatâ€™s been an extremely full on 24 hours in henley on thames!!! such a great night at hotel du vin tonight for my henley book launch. seeing familiar friendly faces was quite overwhelming...but equally amazing.....tonight was probably one of my toughest presentations; very real and powerful.

my message in my self help book is clear. are you living in your truth having faced your fears? do you know what your voice says?

let donâ€™t hold back guide you, gently challenge you to give you hope (hold on pain ends) and free yourself from the shackles that have been holding you back.

so many people to thank for tonight. naz ahsun, vision maker press for being an amazingly supportive and talented publisher. gemma-leigh james, the breakfast show - marlow fm 97.5 radio presenter for guiding the q&a session perfectly. stefan wesley, sigma digital for not only being super supportive with my websites but also last minute.com filming the event. my amazing pa julie green for her steely focus and enthusiasm, vivienne m clark and ross arrowsmith for backing my onward journey. the henley standard for writing an amazing article this week, overwhelming for me in many ways being in my community, but thatâ€™s the point. iâ€™m stepping through my fear, being courageous and brave and standing here wanting my life to give back to our next generation. michaela clarke for supporting me at the henley herald, and last but not least, to hotel du vin henley on thames for 110% supporting me with everything i do, and making this part of my journey special. 
and of course my biggest thanks goes to my audience and my readers.  the support and love as i step into this new phase of life to give my journey back to others is overwhelming.
